187 // "Paranoid" Debug Asserts are meant to only be enabled during specific debugging/work, otherwise would slow down the code too much.
188 // We currently don't have many of those so the effect is currently negligible, but onward intent to add more aggressive ones in the code.

270 // Helpers: Bit manipulation
271 static inline bool ImIsPowerOfTwo(int v) { return v != 0 && (v & (v - 1)) == 0; }
272 static inline bool ImIsPowerOfTwo(ImU64 v) { return v != 0 && (v & (v - 1)) == 0; }
273 static inline int ImUpperPowerOfTwo(int v) { v--; v |= v >> 1; v |= v >> 2; v |= v >> 4; v |= v >> 8; v |= v >> 16; v++; return v; }

305 // Helpers: ImVec2/ImVec4 operators
306 // We are keeping those disabled by default so they don't leak in user space, to allow user enabling implicit cast operators between ImVec2 and their own types (using IM_VEC2_CLASS_EXTRA etc.)
307 // We unfortunately don't have a unary- operator for ImVec2 because this would needs to be defined inside the class itself.
308 #ifdef IMGUI_DEFINE_MATH_OPERATORS
309 static inline ImVec2 operator*(const ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x * rhs, lhs.y * rhs); }
310 static inline ImVec2 operator/(const ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x / rhs, lhs.y / rhs); }
311 static inline ImVec2 operator+(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x + rhs.x, lhs.y + rhs.y); }
312 static inline ImVec2 operator-(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x - rhs.x, lhs.y - rhs.y); }
313 static inline ImVec2 operator*(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x * rhs.x, lhs.y * rhs.y); }
314 static inline ImVec2 operator/(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x / rhs.x, lhs.y / rhs.y); }
315 static inline ImVec2& operator*=(ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { lhs.x *= rhs; lhs.y *= rhs; return lhs; }
316 static inline ImVec2& operator/=(ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { lhs.x /= rhs; lhs.y /= rhs; return lhs; }
317 static inline ImVec2& operator+=(ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { lhs.x += rhs.x; lhs.y += rhs.y; return lhs; }
318 static inline ImVec2& operator-=(ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { lhs.x -= rhs.x; lhs.y -= rhs.y; return lhs; }
319 static inline ImVec2& operator*=(ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { lhs.x *= rhs.x; lhs.y *= rhs.y; return lhs; }
320 static inline ImVec2& operator/=(ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { lhs.x /= rhs.x; lhs.y /= rhs.y; return lhs; }
321 static inline ImVec4 operator+(const ImVec4& lhs, const ImVec4& rhs) { return ImVec4(lhs.x + rhs.x, lhs.y + rhs.y, lhs.z + rhs.z, lhs.w + rhs.w); }
322 static inline ImVec4 operator-(const ImVec4& lhs, const ImVec4& rhs) { return ImVec4(lhs.x - rhs.x, lhs.y - rhs.y, lhs.z - rhs.z, lhs.w - rhs.w); }
323 static inline ImVec4 operator*(const ImVec4& lhs, const ImVec4& rhs) { return ImVec4(lhs.x * rhs.x, lhs.y * rhs.y, lhs.z * rhs.z, lhs.w * rhs.w); }
324 #endif

348 // Helpers: Maths
349 // - Wrapper for standard libs functions. (Note that imgui_demo.cpp does _not_ use them to keep the code easy to copy)
350 #ifndef IMGUI_DISABLE_DEFAULT_MATH_FUNCTIONS
351 #define ImFabs(X) fabsf(X)
352 #define ImSqrt(X) sqrtf(X)
353 #define ImFmod(X, Y) fmodf((X), (Y))
354 #define ImCos(X) cosf(X)
355 #define ImSin(X) sinf(X)
356 #define ImAcos(X) acosf(X)
357 #define ImAtan2(Y, X) atan2f((Y), (X))
358 #define ImAtof(STR) atof(STR)
359 #define ImFloorStd(X) floorf(X) // We already uses our own ImFloor() { return (float)(int)v } internally so the standard one wrapper is named differently (it's used by e.g. stb_truetype)
360 #define ImCeil(X) ceilf(X)
361 static inline float ImPow(float x, float y) { return powf(x, y); } // DragBehaviorT/SliderBehaviorT uses ImPow with either float/double and need the precision
362 static inline double ImPow(double x, double y) { return pow(x, y); }
363 static inline float ImLog(float x) { return logf(x); } // DragBehaviorT/SliderBehaviorT uses ImLog with either float/double and need the precision
364 static inline double ImLog(double x) { return log(x); }
365 static inline float ImAbs(float x) { return fabsf(x); }
366 static inline double ImAbs(double x) { return fabs(x); }
367 static inline float ImSign(float x) { return (x < 0.0f) ? -1.0f : ((x > 0.0f) ? 1.0f : 0.0f); } // Sign operator - returns -1, 0 or 1 based on sign of argument
368 static inline double ImSign(double x) { return (x < 0.0) ? -1.0 : ((x > 0.0) ? 1.0 : 0.0); }
369 #endif
370 // - ImMin/ImMax/ImClamp/ImLerp/ImSwap are used by widgets which support variety of types: signed/unsigned int/long long float/double
371 // (Exceptionally using templates here but we could also redefine them for those types)
372 template<typename T> static inline T ImMin(T lhs, T rhs) { return lhs < rhs ? lhs : rhs; }
373 template<typename T> static inline T ImMax(T lhs, T rhs) { return lhs >= rhs ? lhs : rhs; }
374 template<typename T> static inline T ImClamp(T v, T mn, T mx) { return (v < mn) ? mn : (v > mx) ? mx : v; }
375 template<typename T> static inline T ImLerp(T a, T b, float t) { return (T)(a + (b - a) * t); }
376 template<typename T> static inline void ImSwap(T& a, T& b) { T tmp = a; a = b; b = tmp; }
377 template<typename T> static inline T ImAddClampOverflow(T a, T b, T mn, T mx) { if (b < 0 && (a < mn - b)) return mn; if (b > 0 && (a > mx - b)) return mx; return a + b; }
378 template<typename T> static inline T ImSubClampOverflow(T a, T b, T mn, T mx) { if (b > 0 && (a < mn + b)) return mn; if (b < 0 && (a > mx + b)) return mx; return a - b; }
379 // - Misc maths helpers
380 static inline ImVec2 ImMin(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x < rhs.x ? lhs.x : rhs.x, lhs.y < rhs.y ? lhs.y : rhs.y); }
381 static inline ImVec2 ImMax(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x >= rhs.x ? lhs.x : rhs.x, lhs.y >= rhs.y ? lhs.y : rhs.y); }
382 static inline ImVec2 ImClamp(const ImVec2& v, const ImVec2& mn, ImVec2 mx) { return ImVec2((v.x < mn.x) ? mn.x : (v.x > mx.x) ? mx.x : v.x, (v.y < mn.y) ? mn.y : (v.y > mx.y) ? mx.y : v.y); }
383 static inline ImVec2 ImLerp(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, float t) { return ImVec2(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t); }
384 static inline ImVec2 ImLerp(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, const ImVec2& t) { return ImVec2(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t.x, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t.y); }
385 static inline ImVec4 ImLerp(const ImVec4& a, const ImVec4& b, float t) { return ImVec4(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t, a.z + (b.z - a.z) * t, a.w + (b.w - a.w) * t); }
386 static inline float ImSaturate(float f) { return (f < 0.0f) ? 0.0f : (f > 1.0f) ? 1.0f : f; }
387 static inline float ImLengthSqr(const ImVec2& lhs) { return (lhs.x * lhs.x) + (lhs.y * lhs.y); }
388 static inline float ImLengthSqr(const ImVec4& lhs) { return (lhs.x * lhs.x) + (lhs.y * lhs.y) + (lhs.z * lhs.z) + (lhs.w * lhs.w); }
389 static inline float ImInvLength(const ImVec2& lhs, float fail_value) { float d = (lhs.x * lhs.x) + (lhs.y * lhs.y); if (d > 0.0f) return 1.0f / ImSqrt(d); return fail_value; }
390 static inline float ImFloor(float f) { return (float)(int)(f); }
391 static inline ImVec2 ImFloor(const ImVec2& v) { return ImVec2((float)(int)(v.x), (float)(int)(v.y)); }
392 static inline int ImModPositive(int a, int b) { return (a + b) % b; }
393 static inline float ImDot(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b) { return a.x * b.x + a.y * b.y; }
394 static inline ImVec2 ImRotate(const ImVec2& v, float cos_a, float sin_a) { return ImVec2(v.x * cos_a - v.y * sin_a, v.x * sin_a + v.y * cos_a); }
395 static inline float ImLinearSweep(float current, float target, float speed) { if (current < target) return ImMin(current + speed, target); if (current > target) return ImMax(current - speed, target); return current; }
396 static inline ImVec2 ImMul(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x * rhs.x, lhs.y * rhs.y); }

406 inline float ImTriangleArea(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, const ImVec2& c) { return ImFabs((a.x * (b.y - c.y)) + (b.x * (c.y - a.y)) + (c.x * (a.y - b.y))) * 0.5f; }
407 IMGUI_API ImGuiDir ImGetDirQuadrantFromDelta(float dx, float dy);

427 // Helper: ImRect (2D axis aligned bounding-box)
428 // NB: we can't rely on ImVec2 math operators being available here!
429 struct IMGUI_API ImRect
430 {
431  ImVec2 Min; // Upper-left
432  ImVec2 Max; // Lower-right
433 
434  ImRect() : Min(0.0f, 0.0f), Max(0.0f, 0.0f) {}
435  ImRect(const ImVec2& min, const ImVec2& max) : Min(min), Max(max) {}
436  ImRect(const ImVec4& v) : Min(v.x, v.y), Max(v.z, v.w) {}
437  ImRect(float x1, float y1, float x2, float y2) : Min(x1, y1), Max(x2, y2) {}
438 
439  ImVec2 GetCenter() const { return ImVec2((Min.x + Max.x) * 0.5f, (Min.y + Max.y) * 0.5f); }
440  ImVec2 GetSize() const { return ImVec2(Max.x - Min.x, Max.y - Min.y); }
441  float GetWidth() const { return Max.x - Min.x; }
442  float GetHeight() const { return Max.y - Min.y; }
443  ImVec2 GetTL() const { return Min; } // Top-left
444  ImVec2 GetTR() const { return ImVec2(Max.x, Min.y); } // Top-right
445  ImVec2 GetBL() const { return ImVec2(Min.x, Max.y); } // Bottom-left
446  ImVec2 GetBR() const { return Max; } // Bottom-right
447  bool Contains(const ImVec2& p) const { return p.x >= Min.x && p.y >= Min.y && p.x < Max.x && p.y < Max.y; }
448  bool Contains(const ImRect& r) const { return r.Min.x >= Min.x && r.Min.y >= Min.y && r.Max.x <= Max.x && r.Max.y <= Max.y; }
449  bool Overlaps(const ImRect& r) const { return r.Min.y < Max.y && r.Max.y > Min.y && r.Min.x < Max.x && r.Max.x > Min.x; }
450  void Add(const ImVec2& p) { if (Min.x > p.x) Min.x = p.x; if (Min.y > p.y) Min.y = p.y; if (Max.x < p.x) Max.x = p.x; if (Max.y < p.y) Max.y = p.y; }
451  void Add(const ImRect& r) { if (Min.x > r.Min.x) Min.x = r.Min.x; if (Min.y > r.Min.y) Min.y = r.Min.y; if (Max.x < r.Max.x) Max.x = r.Max.x; if (Max.y < r.Max.y) Max.y = r.Max.y; }
452  void Expand(const float amount) { Min.x -= amount; Min.y -= amount; Max.x += amount; Max.y += amount; }
453  void Expand(const ImVec2& amount) { Min.x -= amount.x; Min.y -= amount.y; Max.x += amount.x; Max.y += amount.y; }
454  void Translate(const ImVec2& d) { Min.x += d.x; Min.y += d.y; Max.x += d.x; Max.y += d.y; }
455  void TranslateX(float dx) { Min.x += dx; Max.x += dx; }
456  void TranslateY(float dy) { Min.y += dy; Max.y += dy; }
457  void ClipWith(const ImRect& r) { Min = ImMax(Min, r.Min); Max = ImMin(Max, r.Max); } // Simple version, may lead to an inverted rectangle, which is fine for Contains/Overlaps test but not for display.
458  void ClipWithFull(const ImRect& r) { Min = ImClamp(Min, r.Min, r.Max); Max = ImClamp(Max, r.Min, r.Max); } // Full version, ensure both points are fully clipped.
459  void Floor() { Min.x = IM_FLOOR(Min.x); Min.y = IM_FLOOR(Min.y); Max.x = IM_FLOOR(Max.x); Max.y = IM_FLOOR(Max.y); }
460  bool IsInverted() const { return Min.x > Max.x || Min.y > Max.y; }
461  ImVec4 ToVec4() const { return ImVec4(Min.x, Min.y, Max.x, Max.y); }
462 };
463 
464 // Helper: ImBitArray
465 inline bool ImBitArrayTestBit(const ImU32* arr, int n) { ImU32 mask = (ImU32)1 << (n & 31); return (arr[n >> 5] & mask) != 0; }
466 inline void ImBitArrayClearBit(ImU32* arr, int n) { ImU32 mask = (ImU32)1 << (n & 31); arr[n >> 5] &= ~mask; }
467 inline void ImBitArraySetBit(ImU32* arr, int n) { ImU32 mask = (ImU32)1 << (n & 31); arr[n >> 5] |= mask; }
468 inline void ImBitArraySetBitRange(ImU32* arr, int n, int n2)
469 {
470  while (n <= n2)
471  {
472  int a_mod = (n & 31);
473  int b_mod = (n2 > (n | 31) ? 31 : (n2 & 31)) + 1;
474  ImU32 mask = (ImU32)(((ImU64)1 << b_mod) - 1) & ~(ImU32)(((ImU64)1 << a_mod) - 1);
475  arr[n >> 5] |= mask;
476  n = (n + 32) & ~31;
477  }
478 }
479 
480 // Helper: ImBitArray class (wrapper over ImBitArray functions)
481 // Store 1-bit per value. NOT CLEARED by constructor.
482 template<int BITCOUNT>
483 struct IMGUI_API ImBitArray
484 {
485  ImU32 Storage[(BITCOUNT + 31) >> 5];
486  ImBitArray() { }
487  void ClearBits() { memset(Storage, 0, sizeof(Storage)); }
488  bool TestBit(int n) const { IM_ASSERT(n < BITCOUNT); return ImBitArrayTestBit(Storage, n); }
489  void SetBit(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n < BITCOUNT); ImBitArraySetBit(Storage, n); }
490  void ClearBit(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n < BITCOUNT); ImBitArrayClearBit(Storage, n); }
491  void SetBitRange(int n1, int n2) { ImBitArraySetBitRange(Storage, n1, n2); }
492 };
493 
494 // Helper: ImBitVector
495 // Store 1-bit per value.
496 struct IMGUI_API ImBitVector
497 {
498  ImVector<ImU32> Storage;
499  void Create(int sz) { Storage.resize((sz + 31) >> 5); memset(Storage.Data, 0, (size_t)Storage.Size * sizeof(Storage.Data[0])); }
500  void Clear() { Storage.clear(); }
501  bool TestBit(int n) const { IM_ASSERT(n < (Storage.Size << 5)); return ImBitArrayTestBit(Storage.Data, n); }
502  void SetBit(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n < (Storage.Size << 5)); ImBitArraySetBit(Storage.Data, n); }
503  void ClearBit(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n < (Storage.Size << 5)); ImBitArrayClearBit(Storage.Data, n); }
504 };

506 // Helper: ImSpan<>
507 // Pointing to a span of data we don't own.
508 template<typename T>
509 struct ImSpan
510 {
511  T* Data;
512  T* DataEnd;
513 
514  // Constructors, destructor
515  inline ImSpan() { Data = DataEnd = NULL; }
516  inline ImSpan(T* data, int size) { Data = data; DataEnd = data + size; }
517  inline ImSpan(T* data, T* data_end) { Data = data; DataEnd = data_end; }
518 
519  inline void set(T* data, int size) { Data = data; DataEnd = data + size; }
520  inline void set(T* data, T* data_end) { Data = data; DataEnd = data_end; }
521  inline int size() const { return (int)(ptrdiff_t)(DataEnd - Data); }
522  inline int size_in_bytes() const { return (int)(ptrdiff_t)(DataEnd - Data) * (int)sizeof(T); }
523  inline T& operator[](int i) { T* p = Data + i; IM_ASSERT(p >= Data && p < DataEnd); return *p; }
524  inline const T& operator[](int i) const { const T* p = Data + i; IM_ASSERT(p >= Data && p < DataEnd); return *p; }
525 
526  inline T* begin() { return Data; }
527  inline const T* begin() const { return Data; }
528  inline T* end() { return DataEnd; }
529  inline const T* end() const { return DataEnd; }
530 
531  // Utilities
532  inline int index_from_ptr(const T* it) const { IM_ASSERT(it >= Data && it < DataEnd); const ptrdiff_t off = it - Data; return (int)off; }
533 };
534 
535 // Helper: ImSpanAllocator<>
536 // Facilitate storing multiple chunks into a single large block (the "arena")
537 template<int CHUNKS>
538 struct ImSpanAllocator
539 {
540  char* BasePtr;
541  int TotalSize;
542  int CurrSpan;
543  int Offsets[CHUNKS];
544 
545  ImSpanAllocator() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); }
546  inline void ReserveBytes(int n, size_t sz) { IM_ASSERT(n == CurrSpan && n < CHUNKS); IM_UNUSED(n); Offsets[CurrSpan++] = TotalSize; TotalSize += (int)sz; }
547  inline int GetArenaSizeInBytes() { return TotalSize; }
548  inline void SetArenaBasePtr(void* base_ptr) { BasePtr = (char*)base_ptr; }
549  inline void* GetSpanPtrBegin(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < CHUNKS && CurrSpan == CHUNKS); return (void*)(BasePtr + Offsets[n]); }
550  inline void* GetSpanPtrEnd(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < CHUNKS && CurrSpan == CHUNKS); return (n + 1 < CHUNKS) ? BasePtr + Offsets[n + 1] : (void*)(BasePtr + TotalSize); }
551  template<typename T>
552  inline void GetSpan(int n, ImSpan<T>* span) { span->set((T*)GetSpanPtrBegin(n), (T*)GetSpanPtrEnd(n)); }
553 };
554 
555 // Helper: ImPool<>
556 // Basic keyed storage for contiguous instances, slow/amortized insertion, O(1) indexable, O(Log N) queries by ID over a dense/hot buffer,
557 // Honor constructor/destructor. Add/remove invalidate all pointers. Indexes have the same lifetime as the associated object.
558 typedef int ImPoolIdx;
559 template<typename T>
560 struct IMGUI_API ImPool
561 {
562  ImVector<T> Buf; // Contiguous data
563  ImGuiStorage Map; // ID->Index
564  ImPoolIdx FreeIdx; // Next free idx to use
565 
566  ImPool() { FreeIdx = 0; }
567  ~ImPool() { Clear(); }
568  T* GetByKey(ImGuiID key) { int idx = Map.GetInt(key, -1); return (idx != -1) ? &Buf[idx] : NULL; }
569  T* GetByIndex(ImPoolIdx n) { return &Buf[n]; }
570  ImPoolIdx GetIndex(const T* p) const { IM_ASSERT(p >= Buf.Data && p < Buf.Data + Buf.Size); return (ImPoolIdx)(p - Buf.Data); }
571  T* GetOrAddByKey(ImGuiID key) { int* p_idx = Map.GetIntRef(key, -1); if (*p_idx != -1) return &Buf[*p_idx]; *p_idx = FreeIdx; return Add(); }
572  bool Contains(const T* p) const { return (p >= Buf.Data && p < Buf.Data + Buf.Size); }
573  void Clear() { for (int n = 0; n < Map.Data.Size; n++) { int idx = Map.Data[n].val_i; if (idx != -1) Buf[idx].~T(); } Map.Clear(); Buf.clear(); FreeIdx = 0; }
574  T* Add() { int idx = FreeIdx; if (idx == Buf.Size) { Buf.resize(Buf.Size + 1); FreeIdx++; } else { FreeIdx = *(int*)&Buf[idx]; } IM_PLACEMENT_NEW(&Buf[idx]) T(); return &Buf[idx]; }
575  void Remove(ImGuiID key, const T* p) { Remove(key, GetIndex(p)); }
576  void Remove(ImGuiID key, ImPoolIdx idx) { Buf[idx].~T(); *(int*)&Buf[idx] = FreeIdx; FreeIdx = idx; Map.SetInt(key, -1); }
577  void Reserve(int capacity) { Buf.reserve(capacity); Map.Data.reserve(capacity); }
578  int GetSize() const { return Buf.Size; }
579 };
580 
581 // Helper: ImChunkStream<>
582 // Build and iterate a contiguous stream of variable-sized structures.
583 // This is used by Settings to store persistent data while reducing allocation count.
584 // We store the chunk size first, and align the final size on 4 bytes boundaries (this what the '(X + 3) & ~3' statement is for)
585 // The tedious/zealous amount of casting is to avoid -Wcast-align warnings.
586 template<typename T>
587 struct IMGUI_API ImChunkStream
588 {
589  ImVector<char> Buf;
590 
591  void clear() { Buf.clear(); }
592  bool empty() const { return Buf.Size == 0; }
593  int size() const { return Buf.Size; }
594  T* alloc_chunk(size_t sz) { size_t HDR_SZ = 4; sz = ((HDR_SZ + sz) + 3u) & ~3u; int off = Buf.Size; Buf.resize(off + (int)sz); ((int*)(void*)(Buf.Data + off))[0] = (int)sz; return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + off + (int)HDR_SZ); }
595  T* begin() { size_t HDR_SZ = 4; if (!Buf.Data) return NULL; return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + HDR_SZ); }
596  T* next_chunk(T* p) { size_t HDR_SZ = 4; IM_ASSERT(p >= begin() && p < end()); p = (T*)(void*)((char*)(void*)p + chunk_size(p)); if (p == (T*)(void*)((char*)end() + HDR_SZ)) return (T*)0; IM_ASSERT(p < end()); return p; }
597  int chunk_size(const T* p) { return ((const int*)p)[-1]; }
598  T* end() { return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + Buf.Size); }
599  int offset_from_ptr(const T* p) { IM_ASSERT(p >= begin() && p < end()); const ptrdiff_t off = (const char*)p - Buf.Data; return (int)off; }
600  T* ptr_from_offset(int off) { IM_ASSERT(off >= 4 && off < Buf.Size); return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + off); }
601  void swap(ImChunkStream<T>& rhs) { rhs.Buf.swap(Buf); }
602 
603 };

928 // Internal state of the currently focused/edited text input box
929 // For a given item ID, access with ImGui::GetInputTextState()
930 struct IMGUI_API ImGuiInputTextState
931 {
932  ImGuiID ID; // widget id owning the text state
933  int CurLenW, CurLenA; // we need to maintain our buffer length in both UTF-8 and wchar format. UTF-8 length is valid even if TextA is not.
934  ImVector<ImWchar> TextW; // edit buffer, we need to persist but can't guarantee the persistence of the user-provided buffer. so we copy into own buffer.
935  ImVector<char> TextA; // temporary UTF8 buffer for callbacks and other operations. this is not updated in every code-path! size=capacity.
936  ImVector<char> InitialTextA; // backup of end-user buffer at the time of focus (in UTF-8, unaltered)
937  bool TextAIsValid; // temporary UTF8 buffer is not initially valid before we make the widget active (until then we pull the data from user argument)
938  int BufCapacityA; // end-user buffer capacity
939  float ScrollX; // horizontal scrolling/offset
940  ImStb::STB_TexteditState Stb; // state for stb_textedit.h
941  float CursorAnim; // timer for cursor blink, reset on every user action so the cursor reappears immediately
942  bool CursorFollow; // set when we want scrolling to follow the current cursor position (not always!)
943  bool SelectedAllMouseLock; // after a double-click to select all, we ignore further mouse drags to update selection
944  bool Edited; // edited this frame
945  ImGuiInputTextFlags UserFlags; // Temporarily set while we call user's callback
946  ImGuiInputTextCallback UserCallback; // "
947  void* UserCallbackData; // "
948 
949  ImGuiInputTextState() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); }
950  void ClearText() { CurLenW = CurLenA = 0; TextW[0] = 0; TextA[0] = 0; CursorClamp(); }
951  void ClearFreeMemory() { TextW.clear(); TextA.clear(); InitialTextA.clear(); }
952  int GetUndoAvailCount() const { return Stb.undostate.undo_point; }
953  int GetRedoAvailCount() const { return STB_TEXTEDIT_UNDOSTATECOUNT - Stb.undostate.redo_point; }
954  void OnKeyPressed(int key); // Cannot be inline because we call in code in stb_textedit.h implementation
955 
956  // Cursor & Selection
957  void CursorAnimReset() { CursorAnim = -0.30f; } // After a user-input the cursor stays on for a while without blinking
958  void CursorClamp() { Stb.cursor = ImMin(Stb.cursor, CurLenW); Stb.select_start = ImMin(Stb.select_start, CurLenW); Stb.select_end = ImMin(Stb.select_end, CurLenW); }
959  bool HasSelection() const { return Stb.select_start != Stb.select_end; }
960  void ClearSelection() { Stb.select_start = Stb.select_end = Stb.cursor; }
961  void SelectAll() { Stb.select_start = 0; Stb.cursor = Stb.select_end = CurLenW; Stb.has_preferred_x = 0; }
962 };

972  ImVec2 OpenPopupPos; // Set on OpenPopup(), preferred popup position (typically == OpenMousePos when using mouse)

1625 // Transient per-window data, reset at the beginning of the frame. This used to be called ImGuiDrawContext, hence the DC variable name in ImGuiWindow.
1626 // (That's theory, in practice the delimitation between ImGuiWindow and ImGuiWindowTempData is quite tenuous and could be reconsidered..)
1627 // (This doesn't need a constructor because we zero-clear it as part of ImGuiWindow and all frame-temporary data are setup on Begin)
1628 struct IMGUI_API ImGuiWindowTempData
1629 {
1630  // Layout
1631  ImVec2 CursorPos; // Current emitting position, in absolute coordinates.
1632  ImVec2 CursorPosPrevLine;
1633  ImVec2 CursorStartPos; // Initial position after Begin(), generally ~ window position + WindowPadding.
1634  ImVec2 CursorMaxPos; // Used to implicitly calculate the size of our contents, always growing during the frame. Used to calculate window->ContentSize at the beginning of next frame
1635  ImVec2 CurrLineSize;
1636  ImVec2 PrevLineSize;
1637  float CurrLineTextBaseOffset; // Baseline offset (0.0f by default on a new line, generally == style.FramePadding.y when a framed item has been added).
1638  float PrevLineTextBaseOffset;
1639  ImVec1 Indent; // Indentation / start position from left of window (increased by TreePush/TreePop, etc.)
1640  ImVec1 ColumnsOffset; // Offset to the current column (if ColumnsCurrent > 0). FIXME: This and the above should be a stack to allow use cases like Tree->Column->Tree. Need revamp columns API.
1641  ImVec1 GroupOffset;
1642 
1643  // Last item status
1644  ImGuiID LastItemId; // ID for last item
1645  ImGuiItemStatusFlags LastItemStatusFlags; // Status flags for last item (see ImGuiItemStatusFlags_)
1646  ImRect LastItemRect; // Interaction rect for last item
1647  ImRect LastItemDisplayRect; // End-user display rect for last item (only valid if LastItemStatusFlags & ImGuiItemStatusFlags_HasDisplayRect)
1648 
1649  // Keyboard/Gamepad navigation
1650  ImGuiNavLayer NavLayerCurrent; // Current layer, 0..31 (we currently only use 0..1)
1651  int NavLayerActiveMask; // Which layers have been written to (result from previous frame)
1652  int NavLayerActiveMaskNext; // Which layers have been written to (accumulator for current frame)
1653  ImGuiID NavFocusScopeIdCurrent; // Current focus scope ID while appending
1654  bool NavHideHighlightOneFrame;
1655  bool NavHasScroll; // Set when scrolling can be used (ScrollMax > 0.0f)
1656 
1657  // Miscellaneous
1658  bool MenuBarAppending; // FIXME: Remove this
1659  ImVec2 MenuBarOffset; // MenuBarOffset.x is sort of equivalent of a per-layer CursorPos.x, saved/restored as we switch to the menu bar. The only situation when MenuBarOffset.y is > 0 if when (SafeAreaPadding.y > FramePadding.y), often used on TVs.
1660  ImGuiMenuColumns MenuColumns; // Simplified columns storage for menu items measurement
1661  int TreeDepth; // Current tree depth.
1662  ImU32 TreeJumpToParentOnPopMask; // Store a copy of !g.NavIdIsAlive for TreeDepth 0..31.. Could be turned into a ImU64 if necessary.
1663  ImVector<ImGuiWindow*> ChildWindows;
1664  ImGuiStorage* StateStorage; // Current persistent per-window storage (store e.g. tree node open/close state)
1665  ImGuiOldColumns* CurrentColumns; // Current columns set
1666  int CurrentTableIdx; // Current table index (into g.Tables)
1667  ImGuiLayoutType LayoutType;
1668  ImGuiLayoutType ParentLayoutType; // Layout type of parent window at the time of Begin()
1669  int FocusCounterRegular; // (Legacy Focus/Tabbing system) Sequential counter, start at -1 and increase as assigned via FocusableItemRegister() (FIXME-NAV: Needs redesign)
1670  int FocusCounterTabStop; // (Legacy Focus/Tabbing system) Same, but only count widgets which you can Tab through.
1671 
1672  // Local parameters stacks
1673  // We store the current settings outside of the vectors to increase memory locality (reduce cache misses). The vectors are rarely modified. Also it allows us to not heap allocate for short-lived windows which are not using those settings.
1674  ImGuiItemFlags ItemFlags; // == g.ItemFlagsStack.back()
1675  float ItemWidth; // == ItemWidthStack.back(). 0.0: default, >0.0: width in pixels, <0.0: align xx pixels to the right of window
1676  float TextWrapPos; // == TextWrapPosStack.back() [empty == -1.0f]

1678  ImVector<float> TextWrapPosStack;
1679  ImGuiStackSizes StackSizesOnBegin; // Store size of various stacks for asserting
1680 };

1682 // Storage for one window
1683 struct IMGUI_API ImGuiWindow
1684 {
1685  char* Name; // Window name, owned by the window.
1686  ImGuiID ID; // == ImHashStr(Name)
1687  ImGuiWindowFlags Flags; // See enum ImGuiWindowFlags_
1688  ImVec2 Pos; // Position (always rounded-up to nearest pixel)
1689  ImVec2 Size; // Current size (==SizeFull or collapsed title bar size)
1690  ImVec2 SizeFull; // Size when non collapsed
1691  ImVec2 ContentSize; // Size of contents/scrollable client area (calculated from the extents reach of the cursor) from previous frame. Does not include window decoration or window padding.
1692  ImVec2 ContentSizeExplicit; // Size of contents/scrollable client area explicitly request by the user via SetNextWindowContentSize().
1693  ImVec2 WindowPadding; // Window padding at the time of Begin().
1694  float WindowRounding; // Window rounding at the time of Begin(). May be clamped lower to avoid rendering artifacts with title bar, menu bar etc.
1695  float WindowBorderSize; // Window border size at the time of Begin().
1696  int NameBufLen; // Size of buffer storing Name. May be larger than strlen(Name)!
1697  ImGuiID MoveId; // == window->GetID("#MOVE")
1698  ImGuiID ChildId; // ID of corresponding item in parent window (for navigation to return from child window to parent window)
1699  ImVec2 Scroll;
1700  ImVec2 ScrollMax;
1701  ImVec2 ScrollTarget; // target scroll position. stored as cursor position with scrolling canceled out, so the highest point is always 0.0f. (FLT_MAX for no change)
1702  ImVec2 ScrollTargetCenterRatio; // 0.0f = scroll so that target position is at top, 0.5f = scroll so that target position is centered
1703  ImVec2 ScrollTargetEdgeSnapDist; // 0.0f = no snapping, >0.0f snapping threshold
1704  ImVec2 ScrollbarSizes; // Size taken by each scrollbars on their smaller axis. Pay attention! ScrollbarSizes.x == width of the vertical scrollbar, ScrollbarSizes.y = height of the horizontal scrollbar.
1705  bool ScrollbarX, ScrollbarY; // Are scrollbars visible?
1706  bool Active; // Set to true on Begin(), unless Collapsed
1707  bool WasActive;
1708  bool WriteAccessed; // Set to true when any widget access the current window
1709  bool Collapsed; // Set when collapsing window to become only title-bar
1710  bool WantCollapseToggle;
1711  bool SkipItems; // Set when items can safely be all clipped (e.g. window not visible or collapsed)
1712  bool Appearing; // Set during the frame where the window is appearing (or re-appearing)
1713  bool Hidden; // Do not display (== HiddenFrames*** > 0)
1714  bool IsFallbackWindow; // Set on the "Debug##Default" window.
1715  bool HasCloseButton; // Set when the window has a close button (p_open != NULL)
1716  signed char ResizeBorderHeld; // Current border being held for resize (-1: none, otherwise 0-3)
1717  short BeginCount; // Number of Begin() during the current frame (generally 0 or 1, 1+ if appending via multiple Begin/End pairs)
1718  short BeginOrderWithinParent; // Order within immediate parent window, if we are a child window. Otherwise 0.
1719  short BeginOrderWithinContext; // Order within entire imgui context. This is mostly used for debugging submission order related issues.
1720  ImGuiID PopupId; // ID in the popup stack when this window is used as a popup/menu (because we use generic Name/ID for recycling)
1721  ImS8 AutoFitFramesX, AutoFitFramesY;
1722  ImS8 AutoFitChildAxises;
1723  bool AutoFitOnlyGrows;
1724  ImGuiDir AutoPosLastDirection;
1725  int HiddenFramesCanSkipItems; // Hide the window for N frames
1726  int HiddenFramesCannotSkipItems; // Hide the window for N frames while allowing items to be submitted so we can measure their size
1727  ImGuiCond SetWindowPosAllowFlags; // store acceptable condition flags for SetNextWindowPos() use.
1728  ImGuiCond SetWindowSizeAllowFlags; // store acceptable condition flags for SetNextWindowSize() use.
1729  ImGuiCond SetWindowCollapsedAllowFlags; // store acceptable condition flags for SetNextWindowCollapsed() use.
1730  ImVec2 SetWindowPosVal; // store window position when using a non-zero Pivot (position set needs to be processed when we know the window size)
1731  ImVec2 SetWindowPosPivot; // store window pivot for positioning. ImVec2(0, 0) when positioning from top-left corner; ImVec2(0.5f, 0.5f) for centering; ImVec2(1, 1) for bottom right.
1732 
1733  ImVector<ImGuiID> IDStack; // ID stack. ID are hashes seeded with the value at the top of the stack. (In theory this should be in the TempData structure)
1734  ImGuiWindowTempData DC; // Temporary per-window data, reset at the beginning of the frame. This used to be called ImGuiDrawContext, hence the "DC" variable name.
1735 
1736  // The best way to understand what those rectangles are is to use the 'Metrics->Tools->Show Windows Rectangles' viewer.
1737  // The main 'OuterRect', omitted as a field, is window->Rect().
1738  ImRect OuterRectClipped; // == Window->Rect() just after setup in Begin(). == window->Rect() for root window.
1739  ImRect InnerRect; // Inner rectangle (omit title bar, menu bar, scroll bar)
1740  ImRect InnerClipRect; // == InnerRect shrunk by WindowPadding*0.5f on each side, clipped within viewport or parent clip rect.
1741  ImRect WorkRect; // Initially covers the whole scrolling region. Reduced by containers e.g columns/tables when active. Shrunk by WindowPadding*1.0f on each side. This is meant to replace ContentRegionRect over time (from 1.71+ onward).
1742  ImRect ParentWorkRect; // Backup of WorkRect before entering a container such as columns/tables. Used by e.g. SpanAllColumns functions to easily access. Stacked containers are responsible for maintaining this. // FIXME-WORKRECT: Could be a stack?
1743  ImRect ClipRect; // Current clipping/scissoring rectangle, evolve as we are using PushClipRect(), etc. == DrawList->clip_rect_stack.back().
1744  ImRect ContentRegionRect; // FIXME: This is currently confusing/misleading. It is essentially WorkRect but not handling of scrolling. We currently rely on it as right/bottom aligned sizing operation need some size to rely on.
1745  ImVec2ih HitTestHoleSize; // Define an optional rectangular hole where mouse will pass-through the window.
1746  ImVec2ih HitTestHoleOffset;
1747 
1748  int LastFrameActive; // Last frame number the window was Active.
1749  float LastTimeActive; // Last timestamp the window was Active (using float as we don't need high precision there)
1750  float ItemWidthDefault;
1751  ImGuiStorage StateStorage;
1752  ImVector<ImGuiOldColumns> ColumnsStorage;
1753  float FontWindowScale; // User scale multiplier per-window, via SetWindowFontScale()
1754  int SettingsOffset; // Offset into SettingsWindows[] (offsets are always valid as we only grow the array from the back)
1755 
1756  ImDrawList* DrawList; // == &DrawListInst (for backward compatibility reason with code using imgui_internal.h we keep this a pointer)
1757  ImDrawList DrawListInst;
1758  ImGuiWindow* ParentWindow; // If we are a child _or_ popup window, this is pointing to our parent. Otherwise NULL.
1759  ImGuiWindow* RootWindow; // Point to ourself or first ancestor that is not a child window == Top-level window.
1760  ImGuiWindow* RootWindowForTitleBarHighlight; // Point to ourself or first ancestor which will display TitleBgActive color when this window is active.
1761  ImGuiWindow* RootWindowForNav; // Point to ourself or first ancestor which doesn't have the NavFlattened flag.
1762 
1763  ImGuiWindow* NavLastChildNavWindow; // When going to the menu bar, we remember the child window we came from. (This could probably be made implicit if we kept g.Windows sorted by last focused including child window.)
1764  ImGuiID NavLastIds[ImGuiNavLayer_COUNT]; // Last known NavId for this window, per layer (0/1)
1765  ImRect NavRectRel[ImGuiNavLayer_COUNT]; // Reference rectangle, in window relative space
1766 
1767  int MemoryDrawListIdxCapacity; // Backup of last idx/vtx count, so when waking up the window we can preallocate and avoid iterative alloc/copy
1768  int MemoryDrawListVtxCapacity;
1769  bool MemoryCompacted; // Set when window extraneous data have been garbage collected
1770 
1771 public:
1772  ImGuiWindow(ImGuiContext* context, const char* name);
1773  ~ImGuiWindow();
1774 
1775  ImGuiID GetID(const char* str, const char* str_end = NULL);
1776  ImGuiID GetID(const void* ptr);
1777  ImGuiID GetID(int n);
1778  ImGuiID GetIDNoKeepAlive(const char* str, const char* str_end = NULL);
1779  ImGuiID GetIDNoKeepAlive(const void* ptr);
1780  ImGuiID GetIDNoKeepAlive(int n);
1781  ImGuiID GetIDFromRectangle(const ImRect& r_abs);
1782 
1783  // We don't use g.FontSize because the window may be != g.CurrentWidow.
1784  ImRect Rect() const { return ImRect(Pos.x, Pos.y, Pos.x + Size.x, Pos.y + Size.y); }
1785  float CalcFontSize() const { ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui; float scale = g.FontBaseSize * FontWindowScale; if (ParentWindow) scale *= ParentWindow->FontWindowScale; return scale; }
1786  float TitleBarHeight() const { ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui; return (Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar) ? 0.0f : CalcFontSize() + g.Style.FramePadding.y * 2.0f; }
1787  ImRect TitleBarRect() const { return ImRect(Pos, ImVec2(Pos.x + SizeFull.x, Pos.y + TitleBarHeight())); }
1788  float MenuBarHeight() const { ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui; return (Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_MenuBar) ? DC.MenuBarOffset.y + CalcFontSize() + g.Style.FramePadding.y * 2.0f : 0.0f; }
1789  ImRect MenuBarRect() const { float y1 = Pos.y + TitleBarHeight(); return ImRect(Pos.x, y1, Pos.x + SizeFull.x, y1 + MenuBarHeight()); }
1790 };

1802  void Restore() const { ImGuiWindow* window = GImGui->CurrentWindow; window->DC.LastItemId = LastItemId; window->DC.LastItemStatusFlags = LastItemStatusFlags; window->DC.LastItemRect = LastItemRect; window->DC.LastItemDisplayRect = LastItemDisplayRect; }

1900 // [Internal] sizeof() ~ 104
1901 // We use the terminology "Enabled" to refer to a column that is not Hidden by user/api.
1902 // We use the terminology "Clipped" to refer to a column that is out of sight because of scrolling/clipping.
1903 // This is in contrast with some user-facing api such as IsItemVisible() / IsRectVisible() which use "Visible" to mean "not clipped".
1904 struct ImGuiTableColumn
1905 {
1906  ImRect ClipRect; // Clipping rectangle for the column
1907  ImGuiID UserID; // Optional, value passed to TableSetupColumn()
1908  ImGuiTableColumnFlags FlagsIn; // Flags as they were provided by user. See ImGuiTableColumnFlags_
1909  ImGuiTableColumnFlags Flags; // Effective flags. See ImGuiTableColumnFlags_
1910  float MinX; // Absolute positions
1911  float MaxX;
1912  float InitStretchWeightOrWidth; // Value passed to TableSetupColumn(). For Width it is a content width (_without padding_).
1913  float StretchWeight; // Master width weight when (Flags & _WidthStretch). Often around ~1.0f initially.
1914  float WidthAuto; // Automatic width
1915  float WidthRequest; // Master width absolute value when !(Flags & _WidthStretch). When Stretch this is derived every frame from StretchWeight in TableUpdateLayout()
1916  float WidthGiven; // Final/actual width visible == (MaxX - MinX), locked in TableUpdateLayout(). May be > WidthRequest to honor minimum width, may be < WidthRequest to honor shrinking columns down in tight space.
1917  float WorkMinX; // Start position for the frame, currently ~(MinX + CellPaddingX)
1918  float WorkMaxX;
1919  float ItemWidth;
1920  float ContentMaxXFrozen; // Contents maximum position for frozen rows (apart from headers), from which we can infer content width.
1921  float ContentMaxXUnfrozen;
1922  float ContentMaxXHeadersUsed; // Contents maximum position for headers rows (regardless of freezing). TableHeader() automatically softclip itself + report ideal desired size, to avoid creating extraneous draw calls
1923  float ContentMaxXHeadersIdeal;
1924  ImS16 NameOffset; // Offset into parent ColumnsNames[]
1925  ImGuiTableColumnIdx DisplayOrder; // Index within Table's IndexToDisplayOrder[] (column may be reordered by users)
1926  ImGuiTableColumnIdx IndexWithinEnabledSet; // Index within enabled/visible set (<= IndexToDisplayOrder)
1927  ImGuiTableColumnIdx PrevEnabledColumn; // Index of prev enabled/visible column within Columns[], -1 if first enabled/visible column
1928  ImGuiTableColumnIdx NextEnabledColumn; // Index of next enabled/visible column within Columns[], -1 if last enabled/visible column
1929  ImGuiTableColumnIdx SortOrder; // Index of this column within sort specs, -1 if not sorting on this column, 0 for single-sort, may be >0 on multi-sort
1930  ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx DrawChannelCurrent; // Index within DrawSplitter.Channels[]
1931  ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx DrawChannelFrozen;
1932  ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx DrawChannelUnfrozen;
1933  bool IsEnabled; // Is the column not marked Hidden by the user? (even if off view, e.g. clipped by scrolling).
1934  bool IsEnabledNextFrame;
1935  bool IsVisibleX; // Is actually in view (e.g. overlapping the host window clipping rectangle, not scrolled).
1936  bool IsVisibleY;
1937  bool IsRequestOutput; // Return value for TableSetColumnIndex() / TableNextColumn(): whether we request user to output contents or not.
1938  bool IsSkipItems; // Do we want item submissions to this column to be completely ignored (no layout will happen).
1939  bool IsPreserveWidthAuto;
1940  ImS8 NavLayerCurrent; // ImGuiNavLayer in 1 byte
1941  ImS8 SortDirection; // ImGuiSortDirection_Ascending or ImGuiSortDirection_Descending
1942  ImU8 AutoFitQueue; // Queue of 8 values for the next 8 frames to request auto-fit
1943  ImU8 CannotSkipItemsQueue; // Queue of 8 values for the next 8 frames to disable Clipped/SkipItem
1944 
1945  ImGuiTableColumn()
1946  {
1947  memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this));
1948  StretchWeight = WidthRequest = -1.0f;
1949  NameOffset = -1;
1950  DisplayOrder = IndexWithinEnabledSet = -1;
1951  PrevEnabledColumn = NextEnabledColumn = -1;
1952  SortOrder = -1;
1953  SortDirection = ImGuiSortDirection_None;
1954  DrawChannelCurrent = DrawChannelFrozen = DrawChannelUnfrozen = (ImU8)-1;
1955  }
1956 };

2038  ImGuiTableColumnIdx DeclColumnsCount; // Count calls to TableSetupColumn()
2039  ImGuiTableColumnIdx HoveredColumnBody; // Index of column whose visible region is being hovered. Important: == ColumnsCount when hovering empty region after the right-most column!
2040  ImGuiTableColumnIdx HoveredColumnBorder; // Index of column whose right-border is being hovered (for resizing).
2041  ImGuiTableColumnIdx AutoFitSingleStretchColumn; // Index of single stretch column requesting auto-fit.
2042  ImGuiTableColumnIdx ResizedColumn; // Index of column being resized. Reset when InstanceCurrent==0.
2043  ImGuiTableColumnIdx LastResizedColumn; // Index of column being resized from previous frame.
2044  ImGuiTableColumnIdx HeldHeaderColumn; // Index of column header being held.
2045  ImGuiTableColumnIdx ReorderColumn; // Index of column being reordered. (not cleared)
2046  ImGuiTableColumnIdx ReorderColumnDir; // -1 or +1
2047  ImGuiTableColumnIdx RightMostEnabledColumn; // Index of right-most non-hidden column.
2048  ImGuiTableColumnIdx LeftMostStretchedColumnDisplayOrder; // Display order of left-most stretched column.
2049  ImGuiTableColumnIdx ContextPopupColumn; // Column right-clicked on, of -1 if opening context menu from a neutral/empty spot
2050  ImGuiTableColumnIdx FreezeRowsRequest; // Requested frozen rows count
2051  ImGuiTableColumnIdx FreezeRowsCount; // Actual frozen row count (== FreezeRowsRequest, or == 0 when no scrolling offset)
2052  ImGuiTableColumnIdx FreezeColumnsRequest; // Requested frozen columns count
2053  ImGuiTableColumnIdx FreezeColumnsCount; // Actual frozen columns count (== FreezeColumnsRequest, or == 0 when no scrolling offset)
2054  ImGuiTableColumnIdx RowCellDataCurrent; // Index of current RowCellData[] entry in current row
2055  ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx DummyDrawChannel; // Redirect non-visible columns here.
2056  ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx Bg1DrawChannelCurrent; // For Selectable() and other widgets drawing accross columns after the freezing line. Index within DrawSplitter.Channels[]
2057  ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx Bg1DrawChannelUnfrozen;
2058  bool IsLayoutLocked; // Set by TableUpdateLayout() which is called when beginning the first row.
2059  bool IsInsideRow; // Set when inside TableBeginRow()/TableEndRow().
2060  bool IsInitializing;
2061  bool IsSortSpecsDirty;
2062  bool IsUsingHeaders; // Set when the first row had the ImGuiTableRowFlags_Headers flag.
2063  bool IsContextPopupOpen; // Set when default context menu is open (also see: ContextPopupColumn, InstanceInteracted).
2064  bool IsSettingsRequestLoad;
2065  bool IsSettingsDirty; // Set when table settings have changed and needs to be reported into ImGuiTableSetttings data.
2066  bool IsDefaultDisplayOrder; // Set when display order is unchanged from default (DisplayOrder contains 0...Count-1)
2067  bool IsResetAllRequest;
2068  bool IsResetDisplayOrderRequest;
2069  bool IsUnfrozen; // Set when we got past the frozen row.
2070  bool MemoryCompacted;
2071  bool HostSkipItems; // Backup of InnerWindow->SkipItem at the end of BeginTable(), because we will overwrite InnerWindow->SkipItem on a per-column basis
2072 
2073  IMGUI_API ImGuiTable();
2074  IMGUI_API ~ImGuiTable();
2075 };

2124  // Windows
2125  // We should always have a CurrentWindow in the stack (there is an implicit "Debug" window)
2126  // If this ever crash because g.CurrentWindow is NULL it means that either
2127  // - ImGui::NewFrame() has never been called, which is illegal.
2128  // - You are calling ImGui functions after ImGui::EndFrame()/ImGui::Render() and before the next ImGui::NewFrame(), which is also illegal.
